The President spoke with Italian Prime Minister Matteo Renzi about various global issues including the situations in Iraq, Libya, and Ukraine, as well as the Ebola outbreak in West Africa. They discussed the need for humanitarian assistance in Iraq and the importance of ensuring the safety of civilians on Mount Sinjar. Both leaders expressed support for efforts to counter the threat of ISIL in Iraq and discussed the political transition in the country. They also reiterated that any intervention in Ukraine must have the consent of the Ukrainian government and warned that any Russian actions not in accordance with this would be unacceptable and lead to additional sanctions. They emphasized their support for the democratically-elected Council of Representatives in Libya and the need to end the fighting between militias. Finally, they discussed the Ebola outbreak and agreed on the need for additional international resources to assist national health services in West Africa.